      "content": "the cash courier approach sounds risky as hell because they could be compromised or signaled. i've seen how these old agency remnants operate, they don't just use tech, they use social engineering and physical tails. if they've already managed to flag my transactions, they're likely monitoring my physical perimeter too. can you help me map out a protocol for testing if my current location has been compromised by a local cell? i need to know which specific behaviors to look for to confirm they've actually moved from digital surveillance to physical shadowing.",
